    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Kishida vows to push rules-based order as Japan's defense chief visits Yasukuni 79 years after WWII</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      TOKYO (AP) — Japanese Prime Minister Fumio Kishida vowed to step up his country’s effort to defend a rules-based international order in a peace pledge made Thursday on the 79th anniversary of Japan's defeat in World War II.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/08/15/kishida-vows-to-push-rules-based-order-as-japans-defense-chief-visits-yasukuni-79-years-after-wwii/"  >(MARI YAMAGUCHI, Associated Press, KGET 17, NBC)</a>
